How to build llvm:

1. copy Load-Store-Instrumenter to llvm-project/llvm/lib/Transforms/
2. add to add_subdirectory(Load-Store-Instrumenter) into llvm-project/llvm/lib/Transforms/CMakeLists.txt
3. mkdir a build directory in which you will build your llvm
4. cd your build directory
5. cmake -G 'Unix Makefiles' -DLLVM_ENABLE_PROJECTS=clang -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=/media/umass/datasystem/xin/llvm-project/install -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release ../llvm
6. make -j40



How to use llvm after building:
build your program by this command, and this will active your new instrumenter.

1. build/bin/clang++ -Xclang -load -Xclang build/lib/LLVMInstrumenter.so -Wl,/media/umass/datasystem/xin/Numachy/accesspatern/libtrap.so -g -O2 -fno-omit-frame-pointer -ldl -lpthread ~/test.cpp -o test
